Offer Overview

By 2050, when the world’s population hits 10 billion, global demand for protein on our dinner plates will increase by up to 80% over current levels. There are rising concerns that there will be a global shortage of protein-rich foods because of global reliance on animal proteins.

Up until now, alternatives to meat have required complex, highly processed and environmentally unsustainable technologies. The industry fails on the two most critical fronts – products do not satisfy what consumers are demanding, and no company can make it work commercially. Without these challenges being overcome, this multi-billion-dollar opportunity will fail.

Taking a unique and better path, Eighth Day Foods has made a global breakthrough with a cutting-edge proprietary technology solution, called Rapid Solid-State Fermentation, that will reset the plant-based protein landscape—delivering what consumers have been demanding - a healthy protein that is affordable, sustainable and that tastes great.

componentInstanceProperties.name: richTextValue
componentInstanceProperties.value:
This technology now enables ready-to-cook proteins directly from pulses and seeds without any of the challenges faced by competitors – all done from 1 seed, in 1 process, in 1 day, under 1 roof.

Rapid Solid-State Fermentation operates on a fraction of the cost base that currently inhibits the industry – both capital requirements and operating costs. This opens the door to nutritious protein-rich products that are both affordable for consumers and highly profitable for producers.

With five years of research and development behind them and with a highly scalable business model, Eighth Day Foods is already in negotiations with both domestic and multi-national food manufacturers and distributors and is now raising a Series A equity round to fund building its capacity to scale its manufacturing and commercial operations.
